The Tamil Tigers embarked on a tour to garner support for peace talks in Sri Lanka.
Swiss officials met with rebel leaders to discuss a federal structure for peace negotiations.
Factional violence within the LTTE has hindered progress in the peace process.
The government released 10 LTTE rebels on bail, signaling a potential thaw in relations.
Japanese envoy Yasushi Akashi is working to restart peace talks between the government and rebels.
The rebels denied involvement in the killing of a Swiss national, emphasizing the need for accurate reporting.
Akashi's visit aims to facilitate dialogue and move towards a peaceful resolution.
